## What is the lifecycle?  

In React, a component goes through a series of **phases** from the moment it is created until it is removed from the DOM.  
During each phase you can run code (e.g., fetch data, set up subscriptions, clean‑up resources) by using **lifecycle methods** (class components) or **hooks** (function components).

---  

## Class Component Lifecycle (Legacy)  

> **NOTE:** Class components are still supported, but most new code uses functional components + hooks.  

### 1. Mounting – component is inserted into the DOM  

| Method | When it runs | Typical use |
|--------|--------------|------------|
| `constructor(props)` | Before mounting | Initialize state, bind event handlers |
| `static getDerivedStateFromProps(props, state)` | Right before render | Derive state from props (rarely needed) |
| `render()` | During mounting | Returns JSX |
| `componentDidMount()` | **After** the component is in the DOM | Data fetching, subscriptions, timers |

### 2. Updating – component re‑renders due to props or state change  

| Method | When it runs | Typical use |
|--------|--------------|------------|
| `static getDerivedStateFromProps` | Before every render (mount + update) | Sync state with prop changes |
| `shouldComponentUpdate(nextProps, nextState)` | Before render | Performance optimization – return `false` to skip render |
| `render()` | During update | Produce new UI |
| `getSnapshotBeforeUpdate(prevProps, prevPrevState)` | Right before DOM changes are committed | Capture information (e.g., scroll position) |
| `componentDidUpdate(prevProps, prevState, snapshot)` | **After** DOM updates | Operate on updated DOM, network requests based on prop changes |

### 3. Unmounting – component is removed from the DOM  

| Method | When it runs | Typical use |
|--------|--------------|------------|
| `componentWillUnmount()` | Before removal | Clean up timers, cancel network requests, unsubscribe |

### 4. Error handling  

| Method | When it runs | Typical use |
|--------|--------------|------------|
| `static getDerivedStateFromError(error)` | When a child throws | Render fallback UI |
| `componentDidCatch(error, info)` | After an error is thrown | Log error details, side‑effects |

